From cb8f554ca2ec81d58ce03e02c6cdf2c881c342ea Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Nadia Chambers <nadia.yvette.chambers@ik.me>
Date: Fri, 20 Mar 2026 22:13:20 +0100
Subject: [PATCH 030/174] =?UTF-8?q?PGCL:=20sparc64=20PAGE=5FMMUSHIFT=3D4?=
 =?UTF-8?q?=20boot=20=E2=80=94=20TSB,=20TLB,=20set=5Fptes,=20hugetlb=20fix?=
 =?UTF-8?q?es?=
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

Fix 10 bugs preventing sparc64 from booting with PAGE_MMUSHIFT=4:

1. TSB asm context clearing (tsb.S, dtlb_prot.S): srlx/sllx used
   PAGE_SHIFT (17) to clear TLB_TAG_ACCESS context bits, destroying
   MMUPAGE sub-page bits. Fault address 0x2ff660 rounded to 0x2e0000
   (128KB boundary), falling below VMA start. Fix: MMUPAGE_SHIFT (13).

2. TSB pre-population data loss (init_64.c): update_mmu_cache_range
   with nr=1 inserted PAGE_MMUCOUNT (16) TSB entries, but only 1 PTE
   exists. Other 15 phantom entries allowed temporary writes; when they
   expired, fresh zeroed pages were allocated, destroying stack data
   (corrupted auxv → garbled brk). Fix: nr=1 inserts 1 TSB entry.

3. sun4v TLB miss TSB hash (sun4v_tlb_miss.S): COMPUTE_TSB_PTR used
   PAGE_SHIFT for hash. Fix: MMUPAGE_SHIFT at 3 call sites.

4. set_ptes PGCL (pgtable_64.h): Custom override didn't handle nr>1
   expansion. Fix: nr*PAGE_MMUCOUNT PTEs with MMUPAGE_SIZE increments.

5. hugetlb 64K (init_64.c): HPAGE_64K_SHIFT(16) - PAGE_SHIFT(17) = -1.
   Fix: guard with HPAGE_64K_SHIFT > PAGE_SHIFT.

6-10. TSB/TLB flush and hash (tsb.c, tlb.c): PAGE_SHIFT→MMUPAGE_SHIFT
   in flush_tsb_kernel_range, flush_tsb_user, copy_tsb, init_new_context,
   tlb_batch_add_one, tlb_batch_pmd_scan.

Also: vDSO size/init fixes, TLBTEMP bypass, THP RSS accounting fix.

Result: sparc64 is the 6th architecture booting with PGCL.
15/15 pgcl-test + 8/8 pgcl-stress = 23/23 PASS, zero kernel warnings.

Co-Authored-By: Claude Opus 4.6 <noreply@anthropic.com>
